Description: Torso of marble naked male figure preserving right leg to above knee. Drilled holes in back, possibly for the attachment of wings. Represenatation of Eros (?).
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir William Matthew Flinders Petrie
Curator's comments: Good parallel of Eros with purple paint from Naukratis (Hogarth et al. 1905, Pl.14.8).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (CB.37) (Phase 3)
